  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Chop the <strong>sweet potato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</strong> </span>(skin on) into small bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/satay-sweet-potato-and-kale-curry-df/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped sweet potato</strong> to a baking tray with 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp]</span><strong> vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give it a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 15-20 min or until the sweet potato is cooked and golden</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/satay-sweet-potato-and-kale-curry-df/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the sweet potato is cooking, boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Heat a large wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> chopped onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/satay-sweet-potato-and-kale-curry-df/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the<strong> ginger</strong></p><p>Dissolve<strong> </strong>the<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong> in 600ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[1L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/satay-sweet-potato-and-kale-curry-df/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>curry powder</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>tomato paste</strong> and <strong>chopped ginger</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Rinse the <strong>red lentils</strong>, add them to the pan with the<strong> vegetable stock</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until the lentils are cooked and tender</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/satay-sweet-potato-and-kale-curry-df/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, separate the<strong> coriander leaves</strong> from the stalks, then chop the <strong>coriander</strong> <strong>stalks</strong> roughly (save the leaves for garnish!)</p><p>Chop the <strong>lime<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half</p><p>Wash the <strong>shredded kale</strong>,<strong> </strong>then<strong> </strong>pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Once the lentils are cooked, add the<strong> shredded kale </strong>to the pan and cook, covered, for a further 3-5 min or until the kale has wilted</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/satay-sweet-potato-and-kale-curry-df/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the kale has wilted, add the <strong>peanut butter</strong> with the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>coriander stalks</strong> and the juice of 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>lime</strong> and stir it all together – this is your <strong>satay kale curry</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lime</strong> into wedges</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/satay-sweet-potato-and-kale-curry-df/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>roasted sweet potato</strong> over the <strong>satay kale curry</strong></p><p>Finish with a dollop of <strong>coconut yoghurt</strong></p><p>Garnish with the<strong> coriander leaves</strong>, <strong>roasted peanuts</strong> and a<strong> lime wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
